Good day HubSpotters :grin:

Currently working on a clients website - busy optimizing the websites performance.

Yes we have a blog.  It seems to flag on both blog pages and regular pillar pages.

I am trying to remove a field of an embedded form using jQuery, (Which was possible last year) -  however, removing any field now, the form won't submit any longer and I get this type of error:  v2.js:4 Uncaught Error: Minified exception occurred; use the non-minified dev environment for the full error message and additional helpful warnings.
    at r (v2.js:4)
    at Object.findComponentRoot (v2.js:3)
    at Object.findReactNodeByID (v2.js:3)
    at Object.c [as getNodeFromInstance] (v2.js:3)
    at r (v2.js:4)
    at t.getDOMNode (v2.js:1)
    at t.componentDidUpdate (v2.js:2)
    at r.notifyAll (v2.js:1)
    at r.close (v2.js:3)
    at r.closeAll (v2.js:4)

Any ideas how to remove a field in jQuery for an embedded form?

Can anybody help me? I have an issue with landing page forms not loading at all. Uncaught SyntaxError: redeclaration of const options is the error message in console. When I click the link it gives me it shows the form script tag. Any ideas?
These where working a few days ago.

there is a Constant in your JS files with name of *options* which is conflicting with the variable is being used in form embedded code.
Please rename that Constant and the issue will be fixed.
Please send me the link and I will review.
